# Custom Virtual DOM (From Scratch)

A lightweight educational project that demonstrates how a Virtual DOM works internally — written in plain JavaScript. It includes virtual element creation, DOM rendering, event handling, and a small interactive UI demo.

## Features

- Custom Virtual DOM implementation
- `createElement` for building VNodes
- `render` function for converting VNodes into real DOM elements
- Built-in event listener support (`onclick`, etc.)
- Simple rerendering mechanism
- Minimal, clean demo UI
- Dependency-free (only Vite for dev server)

## Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/custom-virtual-dom.git
```

## Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

## Run the Project

```bash
npm run dev
```

## Project Structure

```bash
├── vdom/
│ ├── createElement.js
│ ├── render.js
├── main.js
├── index.html
├── global.css
└── README.md
```
